rule.name: Suspicious String Value Written to Registry Run Key
rule.description: Identifies when suspicious values are written to Run and RunOnce registry keys via signed binaries. Run and RunOnce registry keys cause programs to run each time that a user logs on and are often abused by adversaries to maintain persistence on an endpoint.

message: Malicious Behavior Detection Alert: Suspicious String Value Written to Registry Run Key

rule.name: Unusual DLL Extension Loaded by Rundll32 or Regsvr32
rule.description: Identifies instances of RunDLL32 or Regsvr32 loading a DLL with an unusual file extension. Adversaries often abuse those programs to proxy execution of malicious code.

message: Malicious Behavior Detection Alert: Unusual DLL Extension Loaded by Rundll32 or Regsvr32

build.original: version: 8.6.0, compiled: Tue Jan 3 00:00:00 2023, branch: 8.6, commit: e2d09ff1b8e49bfb5f8940d317eb4ac96672d956

rule.name: RunDLL32/Regsvr32 Loads Dropped Executable
rule.description: Identifies when RunDLL32 or Regsvr32 loads an executable that was dropped by commonly abused programs via phishing such as Microsoft Office or Powershell. An adversary may deliver a weaponized Office document to their target that writes and executes a malicious DLL.

message: Malicious Behavior Detection Alert: RunDLL32/Regsvr32 Loads Dropped Executable

build.original: version: 8.6.0, compiled: Tue Jan 3 00:00:00 2023, branch: 8.6, commit: e2d09ff1b8e49bfb5f8940d317eb4ac96672d956

rule.name: Library Load of a File Written by a Signed Binary Proxy
rule.description: Identifies the image load of a DLL file written or modified by a signed Microsoft binary proxy utility such as MSHTA.exe, CertReq.exe or CertUtil.exe. Adversaries may bypass process and/or signature-based defenses by proxying execution of malicious content with signed binaries.

message: Malicious Behavior Detection Alert: Library Load of a File Written by a Signed Binary Proxy

build.original: version: 8.6.0, compiled: Tue Jan 3 00:00:00 2023, branch: 8.6, commit: e2d09ff1b8e49bfb5f8940d317eb4ac96672d956

rule.name: RunDLL32 with Unusual Arguments
rule.description: Identifies unusual instances of RunDLL32 with suspicious keywords or paths in the process command line value. Adversaries may abuse rundll32.exe to proxy execution of malicious code.

message: Malicious Behavior Detection Alert: RunDLL32 with Unusual Arguments

build.original: version: 8.6.0, compiled: Tue Jan 3 00:00:00 2023, branch: 8.6, commit: e2d09ff1b8e49bfb5f8940d317eb4ac96672d956

rule.name: Suspicious Windows Script Interpreter Child Process
rule.description: Identifies unusual windows script interpreter child process which could indicate code injection or other form of malicious code execution via Windows scripts.

message: Malicious Behavior Detection Alert: Suspicious Windows Script Interpreter Child Process
